title.narrative: Accelerating and Strengthening the quality of Malaria Control interventions in Mozambique

description.narrative: Mozambique - Malaria - Ministry of Health of Mozambique - MOH. This program has the following goals: By 2016, halve the malaria morbidity and mortality rates observed in 2009. The objectives of this program are: By 2016, develop the capacity to effectively manage malaria control at central, provincial and district level. By 2016, reach 100% of the population with information on malaria, with at least 60% following best practice malaria prevention and treatment behaviors. By 2016, test 100% of suspected malaria cases presenting in health facilities and communities and treat according to national guidelines. By 2016, strengthen surveillance, monitoring and evaluation systems so 100% of districts provide timely reporting on key indicators based on quality data, for decision-making at all levels. By 2016, 100% of the population has access to at least one malaria prevention method
